matrix.adapterDistribution.tasks

Class LaplacianTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • matrix.adapterDistribution.ITask
      • matrix.adapterDistribution.tasks.LaplacianTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class LaplacianTask
extends ITask
    This class calculates the values of the Laplacian matrix L[i,i] for startRow <= i < endRow. It is used for distributing the Laplacian operation.

    It requires the following data to be shared by means of a IDataShared

    • The input Matrix associated to the key "A"
    • A FactoryMatrix for creating the result matrix associated to the key "factory"

    Author:
    Antonela Tommasel
    See Also:
    MatrixComputationSparseDistributed.laplacian(Matrix), Serialized Form

        public LaplacianTask(int startRow,
             int endRow,
             int colSize)
        Creates task that calculates the Laplacian values for rows ranging between startRow and endRow-1. The matrix is shared using IDataShared and the key "A".
        Parameters:
        startRow - coordinate of the first row to compute the Laplacian
        endRow - coordinate of the last row to compute the Laplacian
        colSize - column size of the matrix to compute the laplacian
